<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4858&amp;p=21479#p21479"><![CDATA[
Came across this Win 10 color changer from<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://rammichael.com/tag/windows-10-color-control">http://rammichael.com/tag/windows-10-color-control</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br /><br />By checking/applying, turns background autocolor to something like wacky 8.<br />More bright colors. Still has dark colors. Just a different mixed set it uses.<br />Some colors could be too bright, if using original 10 menu.<br />Works fine in Classic Shell Menu.<br /><br />The windows border works too, just only 1 pixel wide.<br />Heard that in a future Win10 upgrade, MS will put back selected top border window color,<br />so it would be more noticable at that time.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Mon Aug 24, 2015 8:47 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
