<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4858&amp;p=20593#p20593"><![CDATA[
To get a black theme (for apps)<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.howtogeek.com/222614/how-to-enable-windows-10%E2%80%99s-hidden-dark-theme/">http://www.howtogeek.com/222614/how-to- ... ark-theme/</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br />Custom Themes, I have noticed that windows 8.1 themes will install and work, however they may cause issues (transparency):<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://uxstyle.com/">http://uxstyle.com/</a><!-- m --> - Install this first if you plan on using any custom themes<br /><br />I personally use this theme, which was built for windows 8.1:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.howtogeek.com/222831/how-to-get-colored-window-title-bars-on-windows-10-instead-of-white/">http://www.howtogeek.com/222831/how-to- ... -of-white/</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br />How to modify your accent color (beyond the few colors they have available):<br />Hit win+R; Paste this: <div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">rundll32.exe shell32.dll,Control_RunDLL desk.cpl,Advanced,@Advanced</div><br /><br />Change the Login screen (Note this alters a system file, and thus may potentially (though not likely) break something)<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/PFCKrutonium/Windows-10-Login-Background-Changer/releases">https://github.com/PFCKrutonium/Windows ... r/releases</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Sun Aug 02, 2015 10:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
